item.title: Pacific Northwest Air Jellyfish
item.description: The Pacific Northwest air jellyfish (Aequarea aeronautica) is a species of medium sized jellyfish characterized by their ability of airborne flight. While commonly referred to as a distinct species, the Pacific Northwest air jellyfish is in fact a stage of the common Aequarea aequorea jellyfish. Description Aequarea aeronautica is a large sized jellyfish, with an average size of 6 to 8 inches in diameter. Its habitat ranges from the upper Pacific Northwest in Canada down south to Northern California.
